    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-05T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-05T10:00:00-05:00" n="198"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d198">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/12–551: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BDKE1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bruce</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-05T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 5, 1951—4 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3338. For <persName corresp="#p_MEM1">Martin</persName> from <persName
                        corresp="#p_VLC1">Vass</persName>. No distribution this message outside
                    State Dept. This is background to long report <gloss target="#t_TCC1"
                        >TCC</gloss> mtg being sent by del.<note n="1" xml:id="d198fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <p>1. Decision circulate draft report Mon for consideration by govts before final
                        <gloss target="#t_TCC1">TCC</gloss> mtg December 14 raises question of
                    extent to which you wish to participate in shaping report. <gloss
                        target="#t_FinMin1">FinMin</gloss>s will, of course, come armed with
                    governmental positions and will naturally assume we have done same.</p>
                <p>2. Since report, including controversial country annexes, will be exceedingly
                    bulky and highly classified, hardly practicable cable report, which cld hardly
                    be ungarbled prior to meeting. If you believe State shld see text and offer
                    comments on points where language may be important domestically or in terms
                    foreign relations (assuming we must be prepared for leaks of virtually entire
                    text), suggest you raise this problem. One possibility wld be for me to return
                    with report as soon as available.</p>
                <p>3. Postponement mtg to Thurs due largely to <persName corresp="#p_MJ2"
                        >Monnet</persName>, who must participate in <persName corresp="#p_SM1"
                        >Schuman</persName> Plan debate balance this week. He threatened resign as
                        <gloss target="#t_TCC1">TCC</gloss> member unless schedule delayed, a move
                    which both US and UK reps described as “blackmail”. <gloss target="#t_TCC1"
                        >TCC</gloss> mtg failed provide either showdown or agreement on issue 1952
                    versus 1954.</p>
                <p>4. <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName> has sent long letter to
                        <persName corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName>, as chairman <gloss
                        target="#t_TCC1">TCC</gloss> purporting to prove Fr effort outstanding and
                    winding up with flat demand for 200 million dollars economic aid last half
                    calendar 1951 and 715 million dollars first half 1952, for total of 915 million
                    dollars in US fiscal year 1952. Letter states must be economic aid with
                    counterpart and minimum amount necessary for Fr support 1,512 billion franc
                    defense budget, which he claims is required to meet defense obligations as
                    worked out by <gloss target="#t_TCC1">TCC</gloss>. No indication yet whether
                        <persName corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName> will accept this as part
                        <gloss target="#t_TCC1">TCC</gloss> operation or turn matter over to
                    bilateral <pb facs="0407" n="369" xml:id="pg_369"/> negotiations. <persName
                        corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName> expects deal solely with <gloss
                        target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss> during <persName corresp="#p_MJ2"
                        >Monnet</persName> absence.</p>
                <p>5. We understand <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName> letter to
                        <persName corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName> was sent by him without
                    prior consultation with his colleagues and does not represent Fr Govt position.
                        [<persName corresp="#p_VLC1">Vass</persName>.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BDKE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bruce</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
